juniL2tpDialoutMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniL2tpDialoutMIB.description: The Layer 2 Tunneling Protocol (L2TP) Dialout MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniL2tpDialoutDomainName.name: JuniL2tpDialoutDomainName
JuniL2tpDialoutDomainName.description: The name of an Internet domain. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII graphics character set (codes 32 through 126).

juniL2tpDialoutDormantTimerValue.description: The system-wide maximum dormant time in seconds.

juniL2tpDialoutTargetConfigTable.name: juniL2tpDialoutTargetConfigTable
juniL2tpDialoutTargetConfigTable.description: The entries in this table represent dialout target routes. An IP packet received which maps to a dialout route will initiate a dial-out operation.

juniL2tpDialoutTargetConfigEntry.name: juniL2tpDialoutTargetConfigEntry
juniL2tpDialoutTargetConfigEntry.description: A dialout target route by virtual router and target ID.

juniL2tpDialoutTargetRouterIndex.description: The router index of the virtual router where this target is located. The value of this object can be used to retrieve additional information in the router MIB.

juniL2tpDialoutTargetIpAddress.name: juniL2tpDialoutTargetIpAddress
